edu.ncsu.csc216.backlog.task

Class TaskItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.backlog.task.TaskItem

  • public class TaskItem
extends java.lang.Object
    Maintains information about a TaskItem including: its ID, completion state, title, creator, owner, type, and notes.
    Author:
    Walker Booth, Brian Morris

      • TaskItem

        public TaskItem(java.lang.String title,
                TaskItem.Type type,
                java.lang.String creator,
                java.lang.String note)
        The constructor for TaskItem creates a new TaskItem with values for all fields. If any of the parameters are null or an empty String, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        title - the title of the task
        type - the type of the task
        creator - the creator of the task
        note - the note attached to the task
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any of the parameters are null or an empty String
